article.headline: Arenas scores 35 in loss
article.story: OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) -- Kobe Bryant scored 19 points to help the Los Angeles Lakers close out their preseason with a 97-87 win over the Washington Wizards on Thursday night. The Lakers trailed by a point with under eight minutes remaining before finishing with a 25-14 run. Larry Hughes led Washington with 15 points. Kwame Brown, the Wizards' leading rebounder last season, was out again with a broken right foot. He will see an orthopedist Friday. Washington coach Eddie Jordan was ejected with 1:02 remaining in the third quarter after arguing Jarvis Hayes was fouled. Lamar Odom had 16 points. Tierre Brown and Jumaine Jones had 12 each for the Lakers. Los Angeles (6-2) will open the regular season Tuesday night at home against Denver. The Wizards finished the preseason at 3-5 and will begin the regular season next Wednesday at Memphis.
